cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes a new framework for monocular visual odometry using CNN and Bi-LSTM, which are commonly used in computer vision. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): Visual odometry is a crucial component in robotics, and the paper focuses on improving the accuracy and generalization ability of visual odometry systems. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed framework utilizes deep learning techniques such as CNN and Bi-LSTM to learn the features and geometric relationships from image sequences. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an end-to-end system for monocular visual odometry, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper utilizes neural networks such as CNN and Bi-LSTM to improve the performance of visual odometry, which falls under the scope of neural and evolutionary computing.
